00:28.763 --> 00:33.032
- ROSE: A long time ago
out of the vast darkness,

00:33.034 --> 00:36.802
God created this wonderful
ride we call life.

00:38.172 --> 00:41.807
He filled the world with
an abundance of beauty

00:41.809 --> 00:44.309
and endless possibilities.

00:45.446 --> 00:49.048
And yet we find ourselves
questioning his creation

00:49.050 --> 00:51.283
and our very own existence.

00:53.320 --> 00:58.257
Many people ask themselves
why are we put on this earth?

00:58.826 --> 01:01.126
What is our purpose?

01:01.762 --> 01:03.796
Why must we be challenged?

01:03.798 --> 01:07.132
with are we faced with so
many heartaches and failures?

01:08.335 --> 01:13.405
Why do bad things sometimes
happen to the very best of us?

01:14.408 --> 01:16.475
And what does God have in store?

01:22.817 --> 01:25.150
♪ This little light of mine ♪

01:25.152 --> 01:27.386
♪ I'm gonna let it shine ♪

01:27.388 --> 01:28.654
♪ Let it shine ♪

01:28.656 --> 01:30.255
♪ Let it shine ♪

01:30.257 --> 01:30.756
- Rosie.

01:30.758 --> 01:33.292
♪ Let it ♪

01:33.294 --> 01:34.359
- Come on.

01:38.299 --> 01:39.731
- I don't wanna go.

01:39.733 --> 01:41.500
- Come on, we have to.

01:41.502 --> 01:43.102
It's for Mommy.

01:48.309 --> 01:50.509
(SOFT MUSIC)

02:02.456 --> 02:03.388
- Go.

02:05.192 --> 02:08.660
- ROSE: My family was
my world, my purpose.

02:08.662 --> 02:11.296
They kept me alive and smiling.

02:11.298 --> 02:15.167
They're a constant reminder
of how great God is.

02:15.169 --> 02:18.537
My sons Ryan and Tim were
the most sacred blessings

02:18.539 --> 02:21.206
God has ever bestowed upon me.

02:21.208 --> 02:24.176
I was their protector
and teacher.

02:24.178 --> 02:25.911
I rejoiced when they rejoiced.

02:25.913 --> 02:28.147
I hurt when they hurt.

02:28.149 --> 02:29.882
I watched them in bewilderment.

02:29.884 --> 02:31.283
Clung to them.

02:31.285 --> 02:33.919
Did all I could
to keep them safe.

02:33.921 --> 02:36.388
- Ma, have you gone
yet with the hopscotch?

02:36.390 --> 02:37.823
- ROSE: No, you.

02:37.825 --> 02:38.891
You first.

02:47.301 --> 02:50.402
Ryan, aren't we
going to say grace?

02:52.573 --> 02:55.340
- Is it Thanksgiving already?

02:57.878 --> 02:59.811
- Did you really just say that?

02:59.813 --> 03:01.380
- GRACE: Yes he did.

03:01.382 --> 03:05.317
- Are we gonna have a Bible
study or are we gonna eat?

03:05.319 --> 03:10.255
- TIM: That's enough, Ryan,
you're disappointing mom.

03:11.926 --> 03:13.258
- Thank you, Lord, for this food

03:13.260 --> 03:14.860
that we are about to receive.

03:14.862 --> 03:16.461
Please bless this family.

03:16.463 --> 03:17.329
Amen.

03:17.331 --> 03:18.397
- Amen.

03:25.206 --> 03:27.439
- You see what I saw?

03:27.441 --> 03:28.340
- Yeah.

03:28.909 --> 03:30.409
- It's too bad.

03:31.779 --> 03:34.913
You gonna tell him
or you want me to?

03:34.915 --> 03:36.615
- I'll do it.

03:36.617 --> 03:37.649
- Alright.

03:37.651 --> 03:39.484
Let him know I signed off on it.

03:39.486 --> 03:40.385
- Will do.

03:46.560 --> 03:47.793
You get the email?

03:47.795 --> 03:49.595
- I haven't checked.

03:49.597 --> 03:51.430
- Give it a look.

03:51.432 --> 03:53.432
That's the Goodwin file.

03:53.434 --> 03:55.334
- Did Doctor Harris
sign off on this?

03:55.336 --> 03:56.001
- Yes.

03:56.870 --> 03:57.936
- Okay.

03:58.672 --> 04:00.339
What do you think?

04:00.341 --> 04:03.875
- I think the X-rays
speaks for itself.

04:05.246 --> 04:07.379
How much time do
you think she has?

04:07.381 --> 04:10.515
- DOCTOR: She came
in too late for time.

04:10.517 --> 04:11.450
- Poor thing.

04:12.920 --> 04:17.389
- Yeah, she didn't
even know she had it.

04:17.391 --> 04:18.490
- You want me to?

04:18.492 --> 04:19.423
- No.

04:19.426 --> 04:20.559
I'll do it.

04:21.928 --> 04:24.463
(SOFT MUSIC)

04:25.032 --> 04:27.599
Hello, Mister Goodwin.

04:27.601 --> 04:30.469
Yes, this is Doctor Sherman.

04:30.471 --> 04:34.439
I have the results
of your wife's test

04:34.441 --> 04:38.477
and I would like you both
to come in and see me.

04:38.479 --> 04:41.713
I'd rather discuss that with
you in person, Mister Goodwin.

04:41.715 --> 04:42.781
Okay.

04:42.783 --> 04:43.682
Thank you.

04:46.620 --> 04:48.053
- ROSE: My poor Ian.

04:48.055 --> 04:53.058
With no faith in God, who
would he turn to for comfort?

04:57.698 --> 04:58.897
That's my boy, Ryan.

04:58.899 --> 05:00.799
Company executive, family man.

05:00.801 --> 05:02.501
He had it all.

05:02.503 --> 05:05.037
But just when you're
feeling on top of the world,

05:05.039 --> 05:08.674
darkness may be lurking
around the corner.

05:11.445 --> 05:12.711
- Three.

05:12.713 --> 05:14.546
Two.

05:14.548 --> 05:15.547
Let's go.

05:15.549 --> 05:16.381
Energy, energy.

05:17.451 --> 05:19.084
- This is Robbie
Martin from Odensoft.

05:19.086 --> 05:22.087
I'm calling about our
exciting new Gen 1.1 software.

05:22.089 --> 05:24.089
- I'm calling to tell you about
an exciting new opportunity.

05:24.091 --> 05:25.590
It's called Generation 1.1.

05:25.592 --> 05:27.426
- You see, that's
how a company runs.

05:27.428 --> 05:31.730
Companies run on efficiency
and Gen 1.1 is exactly it.

05:31.732 --> 05:33.598
- This is Robbie from Odensoft.

05:33.600 --> 05:35.901
I need to speak to the accountants
in charge of acquisition.

05:35.903 --> 05:37.536
Hello, hello, hello.

05:37.538 --> 05:39.004
- Just let's get on
the next call please.

05:39.006 --> 05:40.105
- Gen 1.1 Linda.

05:40.107 --> 05:41.940
- Gen 1.1, hi my name is Linda.

05:41.942 --> 05:43.475
I'm gonna be in your area.

05:43.477 --> 05:45.711
I'd like to talk to
you about the Gen 1.1.

05:45.713 --> 05:48.347
- Anything you need
you come to me, okay?

05:48.349 --> 05:49.548
- How am I supposed to know?

05:49.550 --> 05:50.782
- Gotta keep trying.

05:50.784 --> 05:53.652
- Robbie, it's
autograph time, buddy.

05:55.622 --> 05:58.623
- Jay, how many of these
are you gonna ask me to do?

05:58.625 --> 06:00.525
- As many as I want.

06:03.864 --> 06:04.963
Thank you.

06:08.369 --> 06:11.370
Can you just tighten
that up a little bit?

06:11.372 --> 06:13.505
- If you don't like
how I do it, you sign.

06:13.507 --> 06:14.840
- Sorry.

06:14.842 --> 06:16.708
Please carry on.

06:16.710 --> 06:17.609
Thank you.

06:20.614 --> 06:22.114
- That's better.

06:25.486 --> 06:27.519
- Thought you and
Ryan were friends?

06:27.521 --> 06:28.720
- 20 years.

06:28.722 --> 06:30.155
- These guys don't play fair.

06:30.157 --> 06:32.057
They're not altar boys.

06:32.059 --> 06:34.960
- Todd, what are
they talking about?

06:34.962 --> 06:35.961
- Come on, Marty.

06:35.963 --> 06:37.496
Sounds like sour grapes to me.

06:37.498 --> 06:39.431
- I should give your
guys parking spots

06:39.433 --> 06:41.833
they're in my territory so much.

06:41.835 --> 06:43.101
Old man Rogers.

06:43.103 --> 06:44.603
Goodwin and his team.

06:44.605 --> 06:46.538
They've been trying to
steal the Kaufmann account

06:46.540 --> 06:48.006
for a long time.

06:48.008 --> 06:50.175
- I wanna see every one
of your sales managers.

06:50.177 --> 06:52.077
I wanna see your salesmen.

06:52.079 --> 06:53.445
I am livid.

06:58.786 --> 07:00.552
- Morning boss.

07:00.554 --> 07:03.989
- I know your team poached
all those accounts.

07:03.991 --> 07:06.057
- Come on, Marty.

07:06.059 --> 07:08.160
Show me one team
that closes deals

07:08.162 --> 07:10.429
inside their region strictly.

07:10.431 --> 07:12.063
Everybody does it
everywhere okay.

07:12.065 --> 07:14.633
What's the big deal, Marty?

07:20.441 --> 07:23.008
- So who signed the bottom
of those accounts, Jay?

07:23.010 --> 07:24.609
Who signed off?

07:26.713 --> 07:27.579
- Jay.

07:27.581 --> 07:28.447
- JAY: What?

07:28.449 --> 07:30.615
- Who signed the deals?

07:34.588 --> 07:37.673
- That's better.

07:37.674 --> 07:40.759
- Hey, you better give me a
name or you're getting fired.

07:43.063 --> 07:44.162
- Ryan.

07:48.135 --> 07:50.469
Look, it was Ryan's
idea in the first place.

07:50.471 --> 07:55.106
I don't know who signed
'em but it was Ryan's idea.

07:55.108 --> 07:56.575
- WOMAN: Mister
Goodwin, Todd would like

07:56.577 --> 07:58.877
to see you in his office
as soon as possible.

07:58.879 --> 08:00.545
- Todd's just gonna
have to wait a minute.

08:00.547 --> 08:01.880
- Todd isn't waiting
for anything.

08:01.882 --> 08:04.616
Get in the conference now.

08:04.618 --> 08:07.652
- What is going on around here?

08:14.561 --> 08:18.263
- Peko Instruments, Nondo
Cellular, Melville Lumber.

08:18.265 --> 08:21.266
What's this all have
in common, Ryan?

08:21.268 --> 08:23.168
- They're all deals
that my team has done

08:23.170 --> 08:24.102
in the last few months.

08:24.104 --> 08:25.570
What's the problem?

08:25.572 --> 08:27.138
- Yeah, those are
deals your team did

08:27.140 --> 08:29.808
in Long Island outside
of your territory.

08:29.810 --> 08:32.177
You stole the accounts.

08:32.179 --> 08:34.746
- Marty, nobody stole anything.

08:34.748 --> 08:35.881
Okay?

08:35.883 --> 08:37.849
- Explain yourself, Ryan.

08:37.851 --> 08:40.751
- What did Jay have
to say about all this?

08:40.754 --> 08:42.254
- Let's get him in here.

08:42.256 --> 08:44.656
Tell Jay to get in here.

08:50.564 --> 08:53.198
- Jay, would you help
me out here, please?

08:53.200 --> 08:57.936
Explain to Mister English that
all of our deals are good.

08:59.239 --> 09:03.808
- Mister English, all
of our deals are good.

09:03.810 --> 09:05.110
- That's nice.

09:05.112 --> 09:07.012
You know it's bad enough
the economy stinks

09:07.014 --> 09:08.313
and we gotta lay people off,

09:08.315 --> 09:10.849
and we got salesmen out
there just sucking wind,

09:10.851 --> 09:12.817
and we cannot put
a team together,

09:12.819 --> 09:16.988
but you have to assemble
a bunch of thieves.

09:16.990 --> 09:20.992
- Ryan, if you can't offer
me a reasonable explanation

09:20.994 --> 09:23.194
for this then my hands are tied

09:23.997 --> 09:26.565
- Marty, you know as well,

09:26.567 --> 09:29.568
sometimes things
get shuffled around,

09:29.570 --> 09:32.203
but we always do
the right thing.

09:32.205 --> 09:34.239
So all the sudden
you're gonna come at me

09:34.241 --> 09:36.975
and like tell me that
this is a problem?

09:36.977 --> 09:38.944
- You signed the paperwork.

09:38.946 --> 09:41.980
You gave the blessing on
all of these accounts.

09:41.982 --> 09:45.050
You got Jay Greer with
nine of these last quarter.

09:45.052 --> 09:47.052
15 last quarter before that.

09:47.054 --> 09:49.120
You got 16 from Tony Vespa.

09:49.122 --> 09:51.923
21 from the Marino brothers.

09:51.925 --> 09:53.625
En route to number
one in the country.

09:53.627 --> 09:56.027
There's a little pattern here.

09:56.029 --> 09:57.362
A little thievery pattern.

09:57.364 --> 10:00.165
It's your team and
it's your signature

10:00.167 --> 10:03.101
and it's your job on the line.

10:03.103 --> 10:04.235
- ROSE: How quickly sometimes

10:04.237 --> 10:06.605
the course of our lives change.

10:06.607 --> 10:08.373
Little did Ryan know this
was just the beginning

10:08.375 --> 10:10.275
of a very rough road for him.

10:10.277 --> 10:11.743
- I've been with this
company a long time

10:11.745 --> 10:15.380
I made you millions
of dollars, okay.

10:15.382 --> 10:18.750
I've given you
everything I have.

10:18.752 --> 10:19.851
- You're fired.

10:21.788 --> 10:22.988
- Whoa, Marty.

10:24.758 --> 10:28.226
You can't fire the best
manager in the entire office.

10:28.228 --> 10:29.628
- Just did.

10:29.630 --> 10:31.763
Why don't you get
up and get lost?

10:34.301 --> 10:36.001
- Yes sir.

10:36.002 --> 10:37.702
- TODD: Ryan, go
wait by my office.

10:42.175 --> 10:43.842
- Is this really happening?

10:43.844 --> 10:46.378
- We have a pamphlet
if you like.

10:46.380 --> 10:48.246
- Todd, a pamphlet?

10:49.316 --> 10:51.182
- It's not your fault.

10:51.184 --> 10:52.917
It had to be done.

10:52.919 --> 10:54.419
Someone had to take the fall.

10:54.421 --> 10:57.389
- I know it's not
my fault but me?

10:58.191 --> 11:00.692
I'm taking this very personally.

11:00.694 --> 11:03.328
In fact, I'm thinking of coming
over that desk right now.

11:03.330 --> 11:05.330
- Do you want me
to call security?

11:05.332 --> 11:07.666
That the way you
want this to go?

11:07.668 --> 11:09.200
Listen, you'll be alright, Ryan.

11:09.202 --> 11:11.436
You'll land on your feet.

11:12.406 --> 11:14.939
- What happened to you?

11:14.941 --> 11:16.074
You're like a Judas.

11:17.678 --> 11:22.013
I put this company before my
family for the last 26 years.

11:22.015 --> 11:23.448
- We have counselors available

11:23.450 --> 11:27.886
if you feel like you
need to talk to somebody.

11:28.922 --> 11:29.988
- That's it?

11:30.824 --> 11:31.890
- That's it.

11:40.834 --> 11:41.766
- Hey Ryan.

11:44.071 --> 11:45.437
You'll be fine.

11:51.845 --> 11:52.944
- I'll be fine.

11:57.317 --> 12:00.051
(ALARM BUZZING)

12:07.761 --> 12:10.495
- ROSE: He felt such
disappointment and anger,

12:10.497 --> 12:13.898
but chose not to share his
struggles with his wife.

12:13.900 --> 12:17.402
It was never his way to open
up and show his vulnerability.

12:17.404 --> 12:19.471
He needed to let us help him.

12:19.473 --> 12:21.940
To let us into his heart.

12:29.783 --> 12:31.883
♪ This little light of mine ♪

12:31.885 --> 12:34.853
♪ I'm gonna let it shine ♪

12:34.855 --> 12:37.889
♪ This little light of mine ♪

12:37.891 --> 12:40.892
♪ I'm gonna let it shine ♪

12:40.894 --> 12:43.828
(PHONE RINGING)

12:48.335 --> 12:50.001
- Hi, Grace speaking.

12:50.003 --> 12:51.035
- Hi Grace.

12:51.037 --> 12:52.237
It's Judy Flomer.

12:52.239 --> 12:53.204
- Hi Judy.

12:53.206 --> 12:54.372
How are you?

12:54.374 --> 12:55.807
- I'm fine.

12:55.809 --> 12:57.776
I just wanted to
see how everyone is.

12:57.778 --> 13:00.111
How's Ryan holding up?

13:00.113 --> 13:01.312
- We're doing great.

13:01.314 --> 13:03.314
Everything's great around here.

13:03.316 --> 13:04.382
Kids are great.

13:04.384 --> 13:05.850
Ryan's great.

13:06.987 --> 13:08.453
- Where is he now?

13:08.455 --> 13:09.788
- He's at work.

13:09.790 --> 13:11.956
- He got a new job already?

13:11.958 --> 13:13.324
That's great news.

13:13.326 --> 13:15.026
- You didn't pour my coffee?

13:15.028 --> 13:16.461
- I'm on the phone.

13:16.463 --> 13:19.197
- What are you talking about?

13:19.199 --> 13:20.799
Got a new job?

13:20.801 --> 13:24.936
No, he's been working at
the office like everyday.

13:24.938 --> 13:26.971
- You don't know?

13:26.973 --> 13:28.039
Oh.

13:30.577 --> 13:33.011
Todd fired Ryan three days ago.

13:33.013 --> 13:34.078
I assumed you knew.

13:34.080 --> 13:35.180
I'm so sorry.

13:36.483 --> 13:37.882
- I'm so confused.

13:37.884 --> 13:40.251
He didn't mention
anything to me.

13:40.253 --> 13:42.253
- I'm so sorry.

13:42.255 --> 13:44.956
If there's anything I can do?

13:44.958 --> 13:46.124
- Thank you.

13:46.126 --> 13:47.025
Bye.

14:12.419 --> 14:14.018
Hi honey.

14:14.020 --> 14:15.353
- Hey babe.

14:15.355 --> 14:17.188
- How was work today?

14:18.458 --> 14:19.958
- Good.

14:19.960 --> 14:21.192
Great.

14:21.194 --> 14:22.894
- What did you do at work?

14:22.896 --> 14:23.995
- Same ole, same ole.

14:23.997 --> 14:24.629
Why?

14:24.631 --> 14:29.500
- Judy Flomer called me
asking how I was holding up.

14:29.502 --> 14:31.936
I didn't know what she meant

14:33.073 --> 14:37.876
until she told me her
husband fired you on Monday.

14:37.878 --> 14:39.143
You've been putting on that suit

14:39.145 --> 14:42.547
and going to work
for three days now.

14:44.217 --> 14:47.151
- I didn't know how to tell you.

14:47.153 --> 14:50.054
- I find out that not
only you're out of a job,

14:50.056 --> 14:53.191
but you're keeping
secrets from me.

14:54.561 --> 14:57.595
- That's not what
this was about.

15:17.484 --> 15:20.518
- ROSE: Ryan's life was
spiraling out of control

15:20.520 --> 15:23.955
and strain was being
placed on his marriage.

15:23.957 --> 15:28.159
The one person he needed
most was drifting away.

15:49.115 --> 15:49.948
- Hey Ry.

15:49.950 --> 15:50.682
How's it going, man?

15:50.684 --> 15:52.216
- Look at you.

15:52.218 --> 15:54.686
Still going for a run
even in this weather.

15:54.688 --> 15:57.155
- Hey, you know you
gotta stay fit, right?

15:57.157 --> 15:58.489
- Tell me about it.

15:58.491 --> 15:59.457
- So what's going on?

15:59.459 --> 16:02.126
You took off of work today?

16:02.128 --> 16:03.728
- They let me go.

16:03.730 --> 16:05.496
- Get out of here!

16:05.498 --> 16:06.998
You worked down
there far too long.

16:07.000 --> 16:08.566
- So much for loyalty.

16:08.568 --> 16:11.269
- So what are you gonna do now?

16:12.305 --> 16:15.106
- I'll think of something.

16:15.108 --> 16:16.240
- Amen.

16:16.242 --> 16:17.241
Good seeing you.

16:17.243 --> 16:18.977
- RYAN: You too.

16:26.987 --> 16:29.387
- Mommy, how do
you play checkers?

16:29.389 --> 16:31.055
- You don't know how to play?

16:31.057 --> 16:31.756
- No.

16:33.760 --> 16:35.293
- REPORTER: In
the month of June

16:35.295 --> 16:38.663
coming in at one
and a half resell.

16:38.665 --> 16:39.764
Now as we mentioned earlier--

16:39.766 --> 16:41.699
- Daddy, come and play.

16:41.701 --> 16:43.334
- I'm busy, honey.

16:45.171 --> 16:46.604
- Come on, Dad.

16:48.341 --> 16:51.042
- Kids, go upstairs, please.

16:52.078 --> 16:52.610
Please.

16:52.612 --> 16:56.614
- MAN: Most people have
been expecting this figure.

16:56.616 --> 17:00.151
It's just the economy
has gone one way.

17:01.755 --> 17:04.222
- You could make an effort.

17:07.560 --> 17:09.127
Get some rest.

17:10.230 --> 17:14.799
You're driving Chris
back to school tomorrow.

17:14.800 --> 17:17.101
- ROSE: Ryan felt such regret.

17:17.103 --> 17:22.140
His children once adored him
but now they were so distant.

17:22.142 --> 17:24.041
He was no longer their light.

17:24.044 --> 17:27.078
He did not know how
to connect with them.

17:27.079 --> 17:31.315
Their love and admiration
seemed a distance memory.

17:38.224 --> 17:39.724
- You okay, son?

17:42.595 --> 17:44.328
- Just fine, thanks.

17:45.231 --> 17:47.765
- You could've fooled me.

17:47.767 --> 17:50.334
(SOFT MUSIC)

18:10.623 --> 18:13.424
(PHONE RINGING)

18:16.496 --> 18:18.429
- Hey buddy what's up?

18:19.866 --> 18:22.100
I don't understand.

18:22.102 --> 18:24.769
- ROSE: I wished he had
never gotten that call.

18:24.771 --> 18:27.205
That place was a den of vipers.

18:27.207 --> 18:30.374
The callous, cutthroat
corporate world was no place

18:30.376 --> 18:32.343
for his gentle soul.

18:32.345 --> 18:33.344
- Okay, right.

18:34.347 --> 18:36.647
I'll see you tomorrow.

18:36.649 --> 18:37.715
Thanks.

18:43.389 --> 18:44.789
- Who was that?

18:45.692 --> 18:46.791
- Jay.

18:48.194 --> 18:50.228
They want me to
come back to work.

18:50.230 --> 18:52.463
They wanna see me in
the office tomorrow.

18:52.465 --> 18:54.232
- That's good news.

18:55.135 --> 18:56.767
- Maybe it's not
such great news.

18:56.769 --> 18:59.303
I've been demoted to sales.

19:01.474 --> 19:04.408
- Honey, that is still good.

19:04.410 --> 19:05.343
It's a job.

19:07.547 --> 19:09.180
- Absolutely, yes.

19:09.182 --> 19:10.815
I'll talk to you in a second.

19:10.817 --> 19:12.550
Take care.

19:12.552 --> 19:13.451
- Oh!

19:16.689 --> 19:17.755
Woo!

19:18.858 --> 19:19.757
- Another one.

19:19.759 --> 19:21.759
- Absolutely yes.

19:21.761 --> 19:23.461
- Bang 'em.

19:23.463 --> 19:24.595
- Fantastic.

19:24.597 --> 19:26.364
Ooh, looking good baby.

19:26.366 --> 19:29.333
- I'll talk to you at one
o'clock Tuesday afternoon.

19:29.335 --> 19:29.834
Got you.

19:29.836 --> 19:30.735
Thanks a lot.

19:30.737 --> 19:32.170
Got one.

19:32.172 --> 19:33.437
- Hello?

19:33.439 --> 19:34.372
Hello?

19:35.542 --> 19:39.377
- Just representing
an outstanding product

19:40.446 --> 19:43.181
from a company called Oden.

19:43.183 --> 19:44.715
Who am I speaking with?

19:44.717 --> 19:46.817
- Three, two, one.

19:46.819 --> 19:48.219
Phones down.

19:49.489 --> 19:50.621
How many appointments you got?

19:50.623 --> 19:51.589
- MAN: Lucky 13.

19:51.591 --> 19:53.357
- 13, my man.

19:53.359 --> 19:54.859
Alright.

19:54.861 --> 19:56.561
Hey, how many
appointments your guy got?

19:56.563 --> 19:57.728
- 15.

19:57.730 --> 19:58.829
- 15?

19:58.831 --> 19:59.597
You closed them?

19:59.599 --> 20:00.698
- Yeah.

20:00.700 --> 20:02.266
- Very nice.
- Well thank you.

20:02.268 --> 20:02.900
- Congratulations, welcome.
- Thanks.

20:02.902 --> 20:04.368
- Very nice.

20:04.370 --> 20:05.536
Congratulations.
Now beers on you.

20:05.538 --> 20:06.571
How many appointments you got?

20:06.573 --> 20:07.638
- Six.

20:07.640 --> 20:09.440
- One dozen beers.

20:10.777 --> 20:11.876
Beers.

20:12.545 --> 20:13.477
Very nice.

20:13.947 --> 20:15.746
Congrats bro.

20:15.748 --> 20:16.714
Come on man.

20:16.716 --> 20:17.748
We're superstars here.

20:17.750 --> 20:18.849
How many appointments you got?

20:18.851 --> 20:19.684
- 10.

20:19.686 --> 20:20.585
- 10?

20:20.587 --> 20:21.786
Okay, I like that.

20:21.788 --> 20:22.853
That a boy.

20:22.855 --> 20:23.888
Skinny and fat.

20:23.890 --> 20:25.756
How 'bout you?

20:25.758 --> 20:26.724
- 22 big bro.

20:26.726 --> 20:27.925
- 22.

20:27.927 --> 20:29.627
Are you kidding me?

20:29.629 --> 20:30.761
22.

20:30.763 --> 20:33.631
(GROUP CHEERING)

20:36.669 --> 20:38.803
Madeline, how 'bout you?

20:38.805 --> 20:39.837
- None.

20:40.807 --> 20:41.839
Nine?

20:41.841 --> 20:43.474
- No, none zero.

20:44.644 --> 20:48.279
- MAN: Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

20:48.281 --> 20:49.614
- Boo.

20:49.616 --> 20:52.250
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

20:52.252 --> 20:54.018
Come on.

20:54.019 --> 20:55.785
Which one of you guys
here never got a zero

20:55.788 --> 20:57.855
on one of your phone blitzes?

20:57.857 --> 20:59.257
Mister Perfection.

20:59.259 --> 21:01.559
No see, let's be serious.

21:01.561 --> 21:02.460
Exactly.

21:05.999 --> 21:07.431
- RYAN: Don't
worry, sweetheart.

21:07.433 --> 21:09.267
The more you do,
the easier it gets.

21:09.269 --> 21:11.002
- Thank you, Mister Goodwin.

21:11.004 --> 21:13.504
It's all about teamwork, guys.

21:13.506 --> 21:14.905
We're a family.

21:16.542 --> 21:20.278
How about you, Ryan,
how many appointments?

21:20.280 --> 21:21.012
- Two.

21:23.049 --> 21:25.349
- I don't believe you.

21:25.852 --> 21:27.318
Tony.

21:27.320 --> 21:28.819
- Congratulations,
Mister Manager.

21:28.821 --> 21:30.388
- Thanks.

21:30.390 --> 21:31.455
How many?

21:31.457 --> 21:32.423
Give me good news.

21:32.425 --> 21:33.291
- 17.

21:33.293 --> 21:34.025
- 17.

21:34.827 --> 21:37.561
Bang that bell, bro.

21:37.563 --> 21:38.796
- Goodnight, guys.

21:38.798 --> 21:40.298
- Goodnight, Ryan.

21:40.300 --> 21:42.333
- Let me ask you, Ryan.

21:42.335 --> 21:46.537
From manager to cubicle,
what's that like?

21:46.539 --> 21:49.340
- I tell you, Tony, it's
kind of hard to remember.

21:49.342 --> 21:50.308
- You better start remembering.

21:50.310 --> 21:52.076
You gotta make sales.

21:53.079 --> 21:54.979
- ROSE: The devil
has many faces

21:54.981 --> 21:56.981
and many ways to kick
you when you're down.

21:56.983 --> 21:58.449
- Good luck, Ryan.

21:58.451 --> 21:59.884
- ROSE: The last
thing Ryan needed

21:59.886 --> 22:02.053
at this point in his
life was temptation.

22:02.055 --> 22:05.756
- You think now we
can get that drink?

22:05.758 --> 22:07.491
- Maybe, Trace.

22:07.493 --> 22:09.593
I'll let you know.

22:09.595 --> 22:12.430
- Glad you're back, Ry.

22:12.432 --> 22:13.331
- I agree.

22:14.500 --> 22:15.800
- Hey buddy.

22:15.802 --> 22:17.501
- Good to have you back, man.

22:17.503 --> 22:18.736
- Thanks.

22:18.738 --> 22:23.607
- Listen, I was in Todd's
office for 45 minutes.

22:23.609 --> 22:25.409
He almost fired me, too.

22:25.411 --> 22:27.044
- Thank you for trying.

22:27.046 --> 22:29.647
You've always looked out for me.

22:29.649 --> 22:31.649
- What are friends for?

22:33.553 --> 22:34.685
Glad you're back.

22:35.488 --> 22:36.954
- Thanks buddy.

22:38.591 --> 22:39.957
- Tomorrow alright.

22:39.959 --> 22:40.825
- Have a goodnight.

22:40.827 --> 22:42.493
- You too.

22:42.495 --> 22:44.695
(SOFT MUSIC)

22:50.636 --> 22:53.003
- Can you have them
order two more please?

22:53.005 --> 22:54.438
- Two more.

22:54.440 --> 22:58.376
- And I think we're
okay on everything else.

22:58.378 --> 23:00.644
And did you order those
samples for the lab?

23:00.646 --> 23:02.046
- I did.

23:02.048 --> 23:03.781
They said that they would
come back in about two weeks.

23:03.783 --> 23:05.649
- Two weeks, excellent.

23:06.886 --> 23:09.954
- Did you get a chance
to look at Rose's file?

23:09.956 --> 23:11.756
- I did, yes.

23:11.758 --> 23:12.656
- And?

23:14.961 --> 23:16.694
- You had a look at
the chart, right?

23:16.696 --> 23:18.429
- I did but I felt
like you might be able

23:18.431 --> 23:21.399
to see something that
no one else has seen.

23:21.401 --> 23:24.535
- Well you saw that the cancer
has spread to her brain,

23:24.537 --> 23:28.572
her stomach, her lungs, and
now it's in her lymph nodes.

23:28.574 --> 23:30.441
Unfortunately there's
nothing we can do.

23:30.443 --> 23:32.576
I give her maybe a few weeks.

23:32.578 --> 23:33.711
Maybe a month.

23:33.713 --> 23:34.478
- Weeks?

23:35.948 --> 23:38.749
There isn't any trials or
anything that you can put her in?

23:38.751 --> 23:39.884
Anything at all?

23:39.886 --> 23:41.085
- It's too late.

23:41.087 --> 23:42.620
There's no alternative
treatments?

23:42.622 --> 23:44.422
She's done.

23:44.424 --> 23:45.156
Sorry.

23:46.159 --> 23:47.958
- Are you sure?

23:47.960 --> 23:50.628
- Maybe if she came
a little sooner.

23:51.831 --> 23:53.030
I don't understand what
your fascination is

23:53.032 --> 23:54.498
with this patient.

23:54.500 --> 23:56.767
You seem to be taking
this very hard.

23:56.769 --> 23:58.035
- I'm friends with her son

23:58.037 --> 24:00.905
and he's best friends
with my husband.

24:00.907 --> 24:05.443
She's been my spiritual
inspiration for a very long time.

24:05.445 --> 24:06.944
- The next thing to do would be

24:06.946 --> 24:08.646
to look into hospice
care to make--

24:08.648 --> 24:09.880
- No, no hospice.

24:09.882 --> 24:11.582
I've been taking care
of her this whole time

24:11.584 --> 24:13.884
and I'm gonna continue
taking care of her.

24:13.886 --> 24:16.554
I think she would want that.

24:18.191 --> 24:21.592
- Well, I know you're
a woman of faith,

24:21.594 --> 24:25.463
so I hope that can
be of comfort to you.

24:25.465 --> 24:27.698
- I think God will provide.

24:38.211 --> 24:40.644
- Are you telling, Ryan?

24:43.182 --> 24:44.432
- Uh uh.

24:44.433 --> 24:45.683
I want nothing to do with that.

24:46.752 --> 24:50.054
You should stay out of it, too.

24:50.056 --> 24:52.923
Just email Ryan's
dad the results.

24:52.925 --> 24:53.824
- Okay.

24:55.628 --> 24:58.662
Are you going to church Sunday?

25:00.600 --> 25:03.601
- I've got a big
presentation at the office.

25:03.603 --> 25:05.803
- The kids would love
to see you though.

25:05.805 --> 25:06.604
- I know.

25:06.606 --> 25:12.176
The kids would also like to
go on vacation more too right?

25:12.178 --> 25:14.044
You hold down the
fort at church.

25:14.046 --> 25:16.146
I'll keep making money.

25:19.719 --> 25:20.651
Gotta go.

25:24.190 --> 25:25.689
- It's gonna be
great this weekend.

25:25.691 --> 25:26.891
- I can't wait.

25:26.893 --> 25:28.726
- What'd you tell your wife?

25:28.728 --> 25:29.844
- Who cares?

25:29.845 --> 25:30.961
She doesn't listen to me.

25:30.963 --> 25:32.696
She listens to God.

25:32.698 --> 25:35.132
She thinks he's a
better husband than me.

25:35.134 --> 25:36.600
- Apparently.

25:39.205 --> 25:40.838
- Let's see.

25:40.840 --> 25:41.839
Here we go.

25:41.841 --> 25:43.541
- ROSE: I tried to be strong.

25:43.543 --> 25:47.244
I didn't want my family to know
just how sick I really was.

25:47.246 --> 25:48.979
I was the heart of this family.

25:48.981 --> 25:54.184
Any pain or sadness I felt, I
kept it locked inside of me.

25:54.820 --> 25:55.753
- GIRL: Stings.

25:58.558 --> 26:01.959
- And then the
honeybee says oh no.

26:01.961 --> 26:03.627
I'm a honeybee.

26:03.629 --> 26:07.965
I pollinate plants that make
fruits, vegetables, and nuts.

26:07.967 --> 26:09.900
And the little girl says.

26:09.902 --> 26:11.802
- But don't you sting?

26:13.272 --> 26:15.239
- Man, look at him go.

26:15.241 --> 26:16.240
- It's amazing right?

26:16.242 --> 26:17.241
- He's unbelievable.

26:17.243 --> 26:19.209
I don't know how he does it.

26:19.211 --> 26:22.846
- ROSE: The boys
admired their dad.

26:22.848 --> 26:26.250
He was always calm and
thoughtful with them.

26:26.252 --> 26:29.019
He had a knack for saying
the right thing to the boys

26:29.021 --> 26:30.721
while never passing judgment

26:30.723 --> 26:33.624
or uttering a
hurtful word to them.

26:33.626 --> 26:35.893
I sensed that Ryan saw
him as a role model

26:35.895 --> 26:38.996
that he himself never
quite lived up to.

26:38.998 --> 26:40.097
- How you guys doing?

26:40.099 --> 26:42.600
- Everything's great, pop.

26:42.602 --> 26:44.735
- What about you, Ryan?

26:45.871 --> 26:47.605
- Doing okay.

26:47.607 --> 26:49.340
- I don't think so.

26:49.342 --> 26:51.775
- ROSE: A continuing
circle of light.

26:51.777 --> 26:55.279
- Could I have a
word with you please?

26:56.816 --> 26:57.815
- Sure Pop.

27:00.152 --> 27:02.319
- Tim, excuse us, okay?

27:02.321 --> 27:04.021
- You got it, Dad.

27:04.023 --> 27:06.857
- It's not as bad as you think.

27:09.629 --> 27:14.365
- I never had to deal with
anything like this in my life.

27:15.368 --> 27:17.868
It's like everything
is piling up.

27:18.904 --> 27:19.937
- Hi Grandpa.

27:19.939 --> 27:20.838
- Hi baby.

27:26.912 --> 27:30.414
- It's like they don't
even talk to me anymore.

27:30.416 --> 27:34.918
- They're of the age
of independence of you.

27:34.920 --> 27:36.420
It's the way life goes.

27:36.422 --> 27:42.993
- Still for me it's like
everything's happening all at once.

27:45.965 --> 27:48.065
It's like I can't even
breathe, you know.

27:48.067 --> 27:49.900
Like I'm suffocating.

27:51.404 --> 27:54.972
- Ryan, consider
yourself lucky, okay?

27:56.275 --> 27:59.677
You're gonna be noticing people

27:59.679 --> 28:03.047
falling on the right
and left of you.

28:03.049 --> 28:07.351
Friends of yours are
gonna be seeking divorces.

28:11.424 --> 28:13.824
- That's easy for you to say.

28:13.826 --> 28:16.293
You and mom have
been rock solid.

28:16.295 --> 28:17.361
- Yes.

28:18.130 --> 28:19.063
Yes.

28:20.166 --> 28:22.766
Times were easier then, Ryan.

28:23.836 --> 28:27.938
A long time ago my grandpa
gave me this thing.

28:30.810 --> 28:31.775
Look.

28:31.777 --> 28:34.712
I was about 10, 12 years old.

28:34.714 --> 28:36.747
And now it's a stone.

28:36.749 --> 28:38.882
Smooth and polished with life

28:38.884 --> 28:42.920
'cause it was like in
a current of a river,

28:45.391 --> 28:47.291
and that's how we face life.

28:47.293 --> 28:49.426
We try to absorb, look.

28:50.396 --> 28:52.730
I'm gonna give this to you

28:52.732 --> 28:55.899
'cause you're rough
like a rock now.

28:55.901 --> 28:57.234
Like a rock.

28:57.236 --> 28:58.769
But you won't get by that way.

28:58.771 --> 29:02.005
You have to embrace
life, get smooth.

29:02.007 --> 29:03.974
Breathe a little bit.

29:03.976 --> 29:05.809
You can do it.

29:05.811 --> 29:08.879
You don't wanna
remain a rock, do you?

29:08.881 --> 29:11.315
No, no.

29:11.316 --> 29:13.750
You become a polished,
articulate stone

29:14.520 --> 29:18.956
just like your father (LAUGHS).

29:41.247 --> 29:42.179
- Come on.

29:46.051 --> 29:47.684
Okay.

29:47.685 --> 29:49.318
- Are you sure you
know what you're doing?

29:49.321 --> 29:51.855
- I think I remember, yes.

29:53.993 --> 29:54.558
Call it.

29:54.560 --> 29:56.193
- Three, two, one.

29:58.097 --> 29:59.029
Blast off.

30:02.468 --> 30:03.934
- One second.

30:03.936 --> 30:04.868
Ready?

30:15.214 --> 30:16.980
- It's okay, Daddy.

30:27.526 --> 30:29.193
- TIM: Hey Pop.

30:29.195 --> 30:30.093
- Hey.

30:32.097 --> 30:34.031
- You still have this?

30:35.534 --> 30:37.367
You remember it?

30:37.369 --> 30:40.070
(GENTLE MUSIC)

30:49.448 --> 30:52.249
- IAN: What you going
down memory lane?

30:52.251 --> 30:53.884
- I haven't seen this in years.

30:53.886 --> 30:55.586
- Remember you and
your goofy brother

30:55.588 --> 30:58.422
used to fight all
the time over this.

30:58.424 --> 31:00.390
I tried to glue it together.

31:00.392 --> 31:03.360
I think you used to beat him up.

31:03.362 --> 31:06.263
- We shot like a
million of these.

31:08.400 --> 31:10.534
- Time certainly flies.

31:20.246 --> 31:21.311
- So what do you got?

31:21.313 --> 31:22.279
- MAN: What do you got?

31:22.281 --> 31:24.014
Straight up to the six.

31:24.016 --> 31:25.015
- MAN: Come on.

31:25.017 --> 31:25.883
- Thank you.

31:25.885 --> 31:28.085
- Why does Santa always win?

31:28.087 --> 31:30.120
- Why is Santa here?

31:30.122 --> 31:31.154
- That's not Santa.

31:31.156 --> 31:32.422
He just looks like him.

31:32.424 --> 31:33.657
- You must've said
your prayers last night

31:33.659 --> 31:35.325
'cause you're
winning every time.

31:35.327 --> 31:36.960
- That's not it.

31:36.962 --> 31:39.029
Just better than
you guys at poker.

31:39.031 --> 31:40.564
- I gotta newsflash
for you boys.

31:40.566 --> 31:42.032
Prayer has nothing to do with it

31:42.034 --> 31:44.368
and God doesn't care
who's winning a red chip

31:44.370 --> 31:46.303
or a green chip or a blue chip.

31:46.305 --> 31:47.271
- You know I agree with you.

31:47.273 --> 31:48.272
You know why?

31:48.274 --> 31:49.373
'Cause there is no God.

31:49.375 --> 31:50.240
- Whatever You say, Aaron.

31:50.242 --> 31:51.041
There is no God.

31:51.043 --> 31:52.292
That's fine.

31:52.293 --> 31:53.542
- You know, Joe, you're
pretty wishy washy.

31:53.545 --> 31:54.978
Do you believe or
don't you believe?

31:54.980 --> 31:56.546
Would you make up your mind?

31:56.548 --> 31:57.915
- You know what Santa
Claus, give me some proof

31:57.917 --> 32:00.050
and I'll believe in God.

32:00.052 --> 32:00.584
- You want proof?

32:00.586 --> 32:02.119
I'm your proof.

32:02.121 --> 32:05.489
You wanna know when I found
God exists for a fact?

32:05.491 --> 32:07.624
Tet Offensive in 1968.

32:09.228 --> 32:13.597
Company got pinned down,
surrounded by all sides.

32:13.599 --> 32:15.999
Got hit hard every area.

32:17.369 --> 32:19.937
While you were selling cars

32:19.939 --> 32:22.606
and you were doing God
knows whatever it is you do,

32:22.608 --> 32:26.343
me and three guys were in a
foxhole trying to survive.

32:26.345 --> 32:29.146
(BOMB EXPLODING)

32:29.148 --> 32:31.949
(GUNS FIRING)

32:44.196 --> 32:45.996
- Say a prayer again, Ted.

32:45.998 --> 32:48.532
- Our father who art in heaven.

32:48.534 --> 32:50.367
Hallowed be thy name.

32:50.369 --> 32:51.969
Thy kingdom come.

32:51.971 --> 32:54.972
Thy will be done on
earth as it is in heaven.

32:54.974 --> 32:57.641
Give us this day our daily bread

32:57.643 --> 32:59.643
and forgive us our trespasses,

32:59.645 --> 33:02.479
as we forgive those who
trespass against us.

33:02.481 --> 33:06.516
And lead us not into temptation
but deliver us from evil.

33:06.518 --> 33:08.318
Forever and ever amen.

33:09.588 --> 33:11.388
- If you were there,
you'd feel it, too.

33:11.390 --> 33:12.322
Trust me.

33:13.325 --> 33:15.392
Jesus was in my foxhole.

33:16.395 --> 33:17.327
Deal!

33:22.735 --> 33:25.602
(GENTLE MUSIC)

33:35.080 --> 33:39.016
♪ Standing on the
shoulders of the morning ♪

33:39.018 --> 33:40.517
- ROSE: Like myself Ian grew up

33:40.519 --> 33:43.153
a strong disciple of God.

33:43.155 --> 33:47.324
That all changed for him
on a fateful day in 1972.

33:48.660 --> 33:53.630
♪ And that's rising
on the widow's peak ♪

33:54.433 --> 33:58.769
♪ Of the afternoon ♪

33:59.571 --> 34:04.307
♪ It's a long way home ♪

34:04.309 --> 34:06.810
♪ Yeah ♪

34:06.812 --> 34:10.414
♪ It's a long way home ♪

34:10.416 --> 34:12.049
- WOMAN: Oh my God, Brian!

34:12.051 --> 34:14.117
- ROSE: The images
of that dying boy

34:14.119 --> 34:17.087
are with him every day even now.

34:17.089 --> 34:19.723
He never stopped
blaming himself,

34:19.725 --> 34:23.060
nor did he ever
stop blaming God.

34:23.062 --> 34:27.130
He vowed never to step
foot in a church again.

34:46.485 --> 34:48.284
- Dad, what's wrong?

34:50.322 --> 34:53.857
- I have some terrible
things on my mind.

34:53.859 --> 34:55.826
I have awful news.

34:59.098 --> 35:03.166
I hate to tell you but
your mama's very sick.

35:04.736 --> 35:06.369
She has cancer.

35:10.642 --> 35:12.876
She's not gonna make it.

35:14.580 --> 35:16.179
We've known for quite awhile,

35:16.181 --> 35:19.816
but she didn't wanna
make everybody sad.

35:21.653 --> 35:23.587
You know, grieve.

35:23.589 --> 35:24.721
Sorry kids.

35:29.394 --> 35:33.130
Try to keep this
away from Ryan, okay?

35:34.867 --> 35:38.735
He has a lot on his
plate at the moment.

35:45.210 --> 35:48.345
- Tim, these are
from six months ago.

35:51.150 --> 35:53.316
- I have to call him.

35:56.321 --> 35:58.889
(PHONE RINGING)

36:02.161 --> 36:04.227
- RYAN: What's up?

36:12.704 --> 36:14.171
- ROSE: My poor son.

36:14.173 --> 36:16.540
He had so many problems.

36:16.542 --> 36:20.544
It upset me that I only
added to his sorrows.

36:28.887 --> 36:33.390
- You shouldn't have
found out that way.

36:33.392 --> 36:34.291
I'm sorry.

36:35.727 --> 36:37.794
- Doesn't matter, Pop.

36:39.331 --> 36:40.397
- No hope.

36:42.501 --> 36:43.533
Sorry, bud.

36:46.939 --> 36:50.874
- I'm just gonna believe
everything's gonna be okay.

36:50.876 --> 36:54.477
Whatever happens,
you're gonna be okay.

36:55.681 --> 36:57.914
- Are you gonna be okay?

36:59.384 --> 37:00.350
- Yeah.

37:01.453 --> 37:03.653
- I'm gonna take care
of this right now.

37:03.655 --> 37:05.355
This can't go on.

37:05.357 --> 37:08.825
It's gotta stop and
I'm gonna stop it.

37:11.430 --> 37:13.363
I love you.

37:13.365 --> 37:14.431
Okay alright.

37:17.369 --> 37:18.919
Ryan.

37:18.920 --> 37:20.470
- Kids, let's go
and see grandpa.

37:20.472 --> 37:21.404
- Let's go guys.

37:21.406 --> 37:22.572
- See you later.

37:22.574 --> 37:24.241
- See you later.

37:31.550 --> 37:35.552
So, what's going on in
that office is just,

37:35.554 --> 37:38.555
it doesn't compare to
what you've already got,

37:38.557 --> 37:39.823
what you've achieved.

37:39.825 --> 37:42.325
What you've achieved is
this wonderful family

37:42.327 --> 37:44.661
and you have to protect that.

37:44.663 --> 37:46.963
They just don't deserve.

37:46.965 --> 37:52.035
They don't deserve for you to
come home unhappy like that.

37:53.939 --> 37:56.373
I mean the people
in that office,

37:56.375 --> 37:59.509
they're meaningless
in the long run.

37:59.511 --> 38:01.711
They're not important.

38:01.713 --> 38:03.313
Your family is your security

38:03.315 --> 38:06.483
and you have to
make them secure.

38:07.386 --> 38:08.551
That's your job.

38:09.554 --> 38:10.487
Your home.

38:13.525 --> 38:16.510
That's your castle.

38:16.511 --> 38:19.496
The children, you know they
need to see you strong.

38:20.899 --> 38:22.732
You're their leader.

38:22.734 --> 38:24.701
- RYAN: I sure don't
feel like the leader.

38:24.703 --> 38:25.869
- You are, hun.

38:25.871 --> 38:27.070
You are.

38:27.072 --> 38:28.471
You're their leader.

38:28.473 --> 38:29.306
You're strong.

38:29.308 --> 38:31.508
You know what you are?

38:31.510 --> 38:33.343
You're like a palm tree.

38:33.345 --> 38:37.781
You know the palm tree
when there's a hurricane

38:37.783 --> 38:39.983
and it blows it all the way over

38:39.985 --> 38:44.054
and it goes to the ground
but it never cracks.

38:44.823 --> 38:47.457
It comes right up again,

38:47.459 --> 38:51.428
and the stress actually
makes it stronger.

38:56.335 --> 38:57.801
- Grace is pretty upset, huh?

38:57.803 --> 38:59.936
- Yes, she's very upset.

39:00.872 --> 39:02.405
She's a love.

39:03.508 --> 39:07.110
She takes such good care
of you and those children.

39:07.112 --> 39:09.045
You're so lucky to have them.

39:09.047 --> 39:12.048
I love every one of
them like I love you.

39:12.050 --> 39:14.818
I just don't want this
whole thing in that office

39:14.820 --> 39:16.953
to upset what you have.

39:21.693 --> 39:22.792
- Warm enough?

39:22.794 --> 39:23.893
- Yeah I'm fine.

39:23.895 --> 39:24.961
- Hey.

39:27.733 --> 39:29.866
- You beat up on your
brother yesterday?

39:29.868 --> 39:30.734
- No.

39:30.736 --> 39:31.668
- Good.

39:31.670 --> 39:33.503
Hi sweetheart.

39:33.505 --> 39:34.704
- Hi.

39:34.706 --> 39:36.539
- I got some money.

39:36.541 --> 39:37.574
- Hi Grandpa.

39:37.576 --> 39:38.541
- Hi.

39:38.543 --> 39:39.709
Papa is wealthy.

39:40.946 --> 39:43.913
If you're nice to me, I
might give you a dollar.

39:43.915 --> 39:45.715
Don't listen to mama.

39:51.056 --> 39:52.089
Don't go so far.

39:52.090 --> 39:53.123
- GRACE: Ladies, go
and play in the park.

39:53.125 --> 39:54.691
- GIRL: Okay.

39:54.693 --> 39:56.659
- IAN: Who took my 20?

39:58.397 --> 40:00.397
- Thanks for having me.

40:00.399 --> 40:02.932
- Every day is like a
birthday with you around.

40:02.934 --> 40:04.033
- Love that cake.

40:04.035 --> 40:05.001
Save me a piece alright.

40:05.003 --> 40:05.869
Don't eat it all.

40:05.871 --> 40:07.470
- Happy birthday.

40:08.473 --> 40:11.174
- You have frosting
on your face.

40:12.611 --> 40:17.080
- You're supposed to get it in
your mouth not on your face.

40:17.082 --> 40:18.748
- Thanks for the tip, boss.

40:18.750 --> 40:19.682
- WOMAN: Don't listen to him.

40:19.684 --> 40:21.684
He's a complete mess.

40:26.425 --> 40:28.625
- Long live the king.

40:28.627 --> 40:30.093
- Goodness.

40:30.095 --> 40:31.494
- Thank you.

40:35.534 --> 40:36.683
- Look here.

40:36.684 --> 40:37.833
You're still invited
to my daughter's

40:37.836 --> 40:39.869
sweet 16 party tomorrow night.

40:39.871 --> 40:41.438
You'll be there, right?

40:41.440 --> 40:43.840
- Looking forward to it, Todd.

40:45.510 --> 40:47.544
- Well that's wonderful
news, darling.

40:47.546 --> 40:50.513
A nice party oughta
cheer you up.

40:51.850 --> 40:56.619
♪ And it's only gonna
be this simple ♪

40:59.458 --> 41:01.057
- Attention everybody.

41:01.059 --> 41:01.791
Attention.

41:02.794 --> 41:03.860
Is everybody having a good time?

41:03.862 --> 41:05.195
- GROUP: Yes!

41:06.731 --> 41:08.198
- Is everybody
having a good time?

41:08.200 --> 41:09.732
- GROUP: Yes!

41:11.036 --> 41:12.202
- Of course you are.

41:12.204 --> 41:14.137
This a Todd Flomer party right?

41:14.139 --> 41:15.472
- WOMAN: That's right.

41:15.474 --> 41:16.673
- Who gives the best parties?

41:16.675 --> 41:17.774
- MAN: You do.

41:17.776 --> 41:19.142
- The Flomer's do.

41:19.144 --> 41:20.043
- WOMAN: Always.

41:20.045 --> 41:21.978
- Come on up.

41:21.980 --> 41:23.480
My lovely Brittany.

41:23.482 --> 41:26.683
So on this special day
your mom and I would like

41:26.685 --> 41:28.718
to give you a gift.

41:28.720 --> 41:30.720
Are you ready?

41:30.722 --> 41:31.654
- Yes.

41:32.257 --> 41:34.023
- Keys to your brand new car.

41:34.025 --> 41:36.860
(CROWD CHEERING)

41:38.697 --> 41:39.662
Happy birthday.

41:39.664 --> 41:40.730
- Thank you.

41:40.732 --> 41:41.598
- Okay.

41:43.502 --> 41:45.268
Now please, please.

41:46.037 --> 41:47.770
Enjoy the rest of the party.

41:47.772 --> 41:48.771
Thank you again.

41:48.773 --> 41:51.040
(CROWD CHEERING)

41:51.042 --> 41:52.642
♪ And when I finally did ♪

41:52.644 --> 41:56.613
♪ I had a dream
of a dead friend ♪

41:56.615 --> 42:01.684
♪ Who seemed to be
doing fine to me ♪

42:02.287 --> 42:04.521
♪ You lead the way ♪

42:04.523 --> 42:07.156
♪ I'll be behind ♪

42:07.158 --> 42:11.928
♪ I won't think of
what I'll find ♪

42:13.231 --> 42:17.734
♪ I'm walking in
with my eyes closed ♪

42:18.603 --> 42:22.906
♪ Only God in heaven knows ♪

42:24.309 --> 42:28.611
♪ I'm always feeling
better every morning ♪

42:29.915 --> 42:33.883
♪ I can't believe
how I once new life ♪

42:35.220 --> 42:37.086
♪ You'll see me when
your time is come ♪

42:37.088 --> 42:39.956
♪ To finally know what love is ♪

42:39.958 --> 42:41.090
♪ You'll be then ♪

42:41.092 --> 42:43.192
- You doing okay?

42:43.194 --> 42:45.962
- Yeah, doing just fine.

42:45.964 --> 42:46.896
- You sure?

42:48.700 --> 42:51.985
- Yeah why?

42:51.986 --> 42:55.271
- Jay seems to be having a
really good time with your wife.

42:55.974 --> 42:57.206
- We're all good friends

42:57.208 --> 43:00.109
and we've known each
other since high school.

43:00.111 --> 43:01.744
- That's sweet.

43:03.582 --> 43:05.582
- ROSE: Every marriage
has its lowest moments

43:05.584 --> 43:09.252
and this was certainly
it for Ryan and Grace.

43:10.589 --> 43:14.357
- I really think you
should go over there.

43:15.961 --> 43:17.226
- ROSE: Neither of them felt

43:17.228 --> 43:19.896
about each other the
way they once had.

43:19.898 --> 43:22.732
The strains of life
had pushed them apart.

43:22.734 --> 43:26.235
♪ Who's to say anyway ♪

43:28.607 --> 43:30.707
- ROSE: Was their
marriage, flawed as it was,

43:30.709 --> 43:34.844
still worth saving,
still worth praying for?

43:34.846 --> 43:39.749
♪ Always will and
it will always be ♪

43:39.751 --> 43:42.819
♪ As long as you are with me ♪

43:42.821 --> 43:43.853
- Hey buddy.

43:44.956 --> 43:46.823
- I need to talk to you.

43:46.825 --> 43:47.890
- Sure.

43:51.396 --> 43:54.197
- What are you doing
talking to Jay for so long?

43:54.199 --> 43:56.366
- He's your best friend.

43:57.669 --> 43:59.102
- But that's not
what it looks like

43:59.104 --> 44:00.703
in front of everybody else.

44:00.705 --> 44:02.305
I have enough problems at work.

44:02.307 --> 44:04.874
I don't need you
making things worse.

44:04.876 --> 44:06.643
- What's in your head?

44:06.645 --> 44:09.646
I'm just talking with Jay.

44:09.648 --> 44:10.647
It's Jay!

44:10.649 --> 44:12.782
- You're acting like an idiot.

44:12.784 --> 44:14.217
- I'm your wife.

44:14.219 --> 44:15.284
Your wife.!

44:17.956 --> 44:20.857
(GENTLE MUSIC)

44:22.661 --> 44:25.261
- Thanks for ruining my party.

44:26.865 --> 44:27.797
- Jerk.

44:30.402 --> 44:32.368
- Way to go Goodwin.

44:33.338 --> 44:35.938
Brittany, come here.

44:35.940 --> 44:40.977
♪ Again for you ♪

44:44.683 --> 44:49.919
♪ It's times like this that I
know you'll see me through ♪

44:57.962 --> 45:02.999
♪ My heart is hurting
to know your touch ♪

45:03.001 --> 45:08.037
♪ Does heal ♪

45:10.942 --> 45:15.978
♪ So hear this prayer
of praise Lord ♪

45:15.980 --> 45:18.948
♪ As I kneel ♪

45:18.950 --> 45:20.049
- Are we going?

45:22.954 --> 45:24.420
The back tire needs air.

45:24.422 --> 45:29.459
♪ When I think of his goodness ♪

45:30.795 --> 45:35.765
♪ I know you can
do it once again ♪

45:36.968 --> 45:40.803
♪ 'Cause you have
walked on water ♪

45:40.805 --> 45:43.873
♪ Your hand has calmed the sea ♪

45:43.875 --> 45:47.376
♪ The deaf they have
heard your voice ♪

45:47.378 --> 45:50.747
♪ Please God calm
the storm for me ♪

45:50.749 --> 45:53.883
♪ And you have fed
the thousands ♪

45:53.885 --> 45:57.887
♪ Strengthen those
ones who are weak ♪

45:57.889 --> 46:02.058
♪ All I ask is for
your forgiveness ♪

46:02.060 --> 46:06.429
♪ And to calm this
storm for me ♪

46:14.906 --> 46:15.538
- Come on.

46:16.775 --> 46:19.842
- First day of the
month roll call.

46:19.844 --> 46:21.778
Let's hear some
good numbers okay.

46:21.780 --> 46:23.946
- 16 units for 350,000.

46:26.050 --> 46:26.949
- TODD: Very nice.

46:26.951 --> 46:29.318
- 41 units, 310,000.

46:29.320 --> 46:31.087
- 34 units, 360,000.

46:33.992 --> 46:35.958
- 27 units, 290,000.

46:39.364 --> 46:41.164
- 51 units, 680,000.

46:43.067 --> 46:44.200
- TODD: Wow.

46:46.337 --> 46:47.436
- Teresa.

46:48.106 --> 46:49.272
- Pass.

46:49.274 --> 46:51.040
- 13 units, 240,000.

46:55.580 --> 46:57.580
- Alright, what's
the total, Pauline?

46:57.582 --> 47:00.049
- 119 units, 1.64 million.

47:03.288 --> 47:04.320
- MAN: Ryan?

47:04.322 --> 47:05.988
- He's not here?

47:09.227 --> 47:11.227
Guys, nice solid month.

47:11.229 --> 47:13.996
But listen, we're this
close from winning

47:13.998 --> 47:16.499
the national sales
leadership award.

47:16.501 --> 47:20.870
All we need to do is get
these guys off the wall.

47:20.872 --> 47:22.972
And we should get it.

47:22.974 --> 47:23.539
Alright?

47:23.541 --> 47:28.377
Don't forget we have the
office football game coming up

47:28.379 --> 47:29.612
and you know I'm a sore loser.

47:29.614 --> 47:31.547
I don't wanna lose.

47:31.549 --> 47:33.282
It's against Long Island.

47:33.284 --> 47:34.317
We can take them, right?

47:34.319 --> 47:35.084
- GROUP: Oh yeah.

47:39.924 --> 47:43.593
- TODD: Let's have
a great month, guys.

47:47.498 --> 47:49.198
- Todd, I'm sorry about Ryan.

47:49.200 --> 47:50.333
- Where is he?

47:50.335 --> 47:53.069
- He's not answering his phone.

47:56.507 --> 47:57.440
- Here you go, boss.

47:57.442 --> 47:58.908
- What's this?

47:58.910 --> 48:00.643
- Marty wanted you to
authorize his transfer.

48:00.645 --> 48:02.912
Back to Long Island.

48:08.486 --> 48:09.385
- Here you go.

48:09.387 --> 48:10.286
- Thanks.

48:18.129 --> 48:19.028
- Gentlemen.

48:19.030 --> 48:20.496
- Where you been?

48:20.498 --> 48:22.565
I been calling you all morning.

48:22.567 --> 48:24.100
- I apologize.

48:24.102 --> 48:27.637
I'm a little rusty and
kind of stressed out.

48:31.142 --> 48:32.108
- Lots of it.

48:34.312 --> 48:38.614
- Nobody misses my monthly
sales roll call meeting ever.

48:38.616 --> 48:40.283
- I apologize, Todd.

48:40.285 --> 48:42.385
It won't happen again.

48:42.387 --> 48:43.686
- You know what?

48:43.688 --> 48:46.188
I don't accept your apology.

48:50.261 --> 48:52.962
- Ry, is everything alright?

48:57.335 --> 48:59.001
Get it together.

49:12.617 --> 49:15.618
- ROSE: My son had
hit rock bottom.

49:15.620 --> 49:18.187
He could not succeed at work.

49:18.189 --> 49:20.189
His marriage was in ruins.

49:20.191 --> 49:23.292
His children had
lost sight of him.

49:24.595 --> 49:27.330
And the one person that
loved him unconditionally,

49:27.332 --> 49:31.200
who saw his greatness even
through his shortcomings,

49:31.202 --> 49:32.201
she was dying.

49:33.438 --> 49:37.006
I wanted to hold him, to
bandage up his bruises

49:37.008 --> 49:41.010
like when he was a
child, but I was weak

49:41.012 --> 49:43.646
and clinging to life myself.

49:44.749 --> 49:48.050
The end of my days
were approaching.

49:48.052 --> 49:51.454
Who would he run
to in my absence?

49:51.456 --> 49:54.156
(GENTLE MUSIC)

49:58.629 --> 49:59.729
- Stop.

50:02.166 --> 50:03.632
This one is right.

50:04.635 --> 50:05.735
There.

50:12.343 --> 50:13.275
See.

50:17.148 --> 50:18.180
It's so heavy.

50:20.251 --> 50:22.251
- This one is purple.

50:23.154 --> 50:24.220
Can you do it?

50:26.357 --> 50:27.556
Perfect.

50:27.558 --> 50:28.691
- Yes.

50:28.693 --> 50:31.160
- GRACE: Perfect.

50:31.162 --> 50:32.261
Really great.

50:33.364 --> 50:34.296
- I hope.

50:44.575 --> 50:46.175
- WOMAN: What's happening?

50:46.177 --> 50:47.610
- Oh nothing.

50:47.612 --> 50:50.179
We're just doing some work.

50:51.482 --> 50:52.681
What are you doing home?

50:52.683 --> 50:54.383
- In our own home?

50:54.385 --> 50:57.720
I just got off work
and I came home.

50:59.757 --> 51:01.323
- Should I go?

51:02.593 --> 51:05.194
- No, Gia just stick around.

51:05.196 --> 51:07.530
We're gonna finish that report
for Todd in a couple seconds.

51:07.532 --> 51:11.233
- No, you should definitely
leave and take him with you.

51:11.235 --> 51:13.335
There's the door.

51:13.337 --> 51:16.238
- No, you should leave.

51:16.240 --> 51:17.673
- Excuse me?

51:17.675 --> 51:19.175
Are you kidding me?

51:19.177 --> 51:21.343
She just told me to
leave my own home!

51:21.345 --> 51:22.812
- We're just doing
some work alright.

51:22.814 --> 51:24.513
You're coming in here screaming.

51:24.515 --> 51:25.614
Stay where you are.

51:25.616 --> 51:27.083
Don't worry about it.

51:27.085 --> 51:30.086
- Jay, you are a
horrible, horrible person.

51:30.088 --> 51:30.753
You hurt your friends.

51:30.755 --> 51:32.288
You hurt me.

51:32.290 --> 51:34.757
I will not allow you
to hurt our children.

51:34.759 --> 51:37.493
- They are my children
and this is my house.

51:37.495 --> 51:39.095
Get out.

51:39.097 --> 51:42.098
- Jay, I have been praying
for you for such a long time

51:42.100 --> 51:43.466
and this is how you repay me?

51:43.468 --> 51:46.302
You bring someone like
this in our house.

51:46.304 --> 51:47.503
Our house.

51:47.505 --> 51:49.138
Do you understand this?

51:49.140 --> 51:51.240
- We are just doing some work.

51:51.242 --> 51:53.176
- Why Jay?

51:53.177 --> 51:55.111
It's clear you're not
just doing some work.

51:55.113 --> 51:56.112
You haven't been doing some work

51:56.114 --> 51:57.580
for a long time, haven't you?

51:57.582 --> 51:59.215
Why Jay?
- We are working.

51:59.217 --> 52:01.650
- God put us together and we
are going to stay together.

52:01.652 --> 52:02.885
Do you understand that?

52:02.887 --> 52:05.287
Jay, come and talk to me.

52:05.823 --> 52:07.656
Tell me what's happening.

52:07.658 --> 52:11.460
- Maybe you should just
take it up with God.

52:13.798 --> 52:17.299
- You are not worthy
of any of us, Jay.

52:18.569 --> 52:20.336
- Sorry about that.

52:27.578 --> 52:30.346
(SOFT MUSIC)

52:39.223 --> 52:42.791
♪ I need thee every hour ♪

52:44.829 --> 52:47.163
- ROSE: Not every story
has a happy ending,

52:47.165 --> 52:49.265
but life does go on.

52:49.267 --> 52:51.167
She was embarking
on a new journey

52:51.169 --> 52:54.837
not knowing what lied
around the corner for her.

52:54.839 --> 52:57.306
In her hour of
darkness, she was brave,

52:57.308 --> 53:00.276
and knew God would
not abandon her.

53:00.278 --> 53:02.578
Life is never easy
for any of us,

53:02.580 --> 53:04.180
but she had the kind of faith

53:04.182 --> 53:06.882
that I wished Ryan and Ian had.

53:07.718 --> 53:12.188
♪ Every hour I need thee ♪

53:12.190 --> 53:17.226
♪ Oh bless me now my Savior ♪

53:17.695 --> 53:19.895
♪ I come ♪

53:19.897 --> 53:21.497
- MAN: Girls do me a favor.

53:21.499 --> 53:23.966
Wait for me in the hall.

