odd sequence of events,

01:08:44.587 --> 01:08:45.854
he shares with me that he thinks

01:08:45.856 --> 01:08:48.490
I should be doing some writing

01:08:49.826 --> 01:08:53.461
and because of this one
in a million coincidence

01:08:53.462 --> 01:08:57.265
of running into him, he
shares something with me

01:08:57.267 --> 01:09:00.734
that well it's really
got me thinking.

01:09:02.572 --> 01:09:05.607
- There is no coincidence, Ryan.

01:09:05.609 --> 01:09:10.345
Coincidence is just God's
way of remaining anonymous.

01:09:16.553 --> 01:09:18.819
- ROSE: Ryan had an epiphany.

01:09:18.822 --> 01:09:21.756
Things suddenly
began to make sense.

01:09:21.758 --> 01:09:24.292
God had filled his
heart and his mind

01:09:24.294 --> 01:09:29.264
and as he took pen to hand,
he and the Almighty co-wrote

01:09:29.265 --> 01:09:33.334
the story of his struggles
and his redemption.

01:09:42.712 --> 01:09:45.412
- WOMAN: You look
beautiful, Rose.

01:09:45.415 --> 01:09:46.915
- So sweet.

01:09:46.917 --> 01:09:49.450
